@host = https://vc.factorlabs.pl

### configuration
GET {{host}}/.well-known/openid-configuration

### keys
GET {{host}}/.well-known/keys

### Source (partner) token — used as the client_assertion for the multi-tenant app
POST {{host}}/api/workload/token


{
  "id": "03de712e-67fc-4d48-8dce-14466f8e219f",
  "aud": "api://AzureADTokenExchange",
  "sub": "system:serviceaccount:default:play-with-workload-identity",
  "subject": "system:serviceaccount:default:play-with-workload-identity"
}

### Target tenant — the multi-tenant SecretMonitor app must be provisioned here
### (see external_tenant/ Terraform) with Application.Read.All admin-consented.
@tenantId = YOUR_TARGET_TENANT_ID_HERE

### Multi-tenant app client_id from `terraform output -raw multitenant_client_id`
@clientId = YOUR_MULTITENANT_CLIENT_ID_HERE

### Paste the JWT returned by the POST {{host}}/api/workload/token request above
@subjectToken = YOUR_SUBJECT_TOKEN_HERE

### Token exchange against the target tenant
POST https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenantId}}/oauth2/v2.0/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

client_id={{clientId}}&
client_assertion_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:client-assertion-type:jwt-bearer&
client_assertion={{subjectToken}}&
grant_type=client_credentials&
scope=https://graph.microsoft.com/.default

### Example Response:
# {
#   "token_type": "Bearer",
#   "expires_in": 3599,
#   "ext_expires_in": 3599,
#   "access_token": "eyJ0eXAiOiJKV..."
# }


@access_token =
### List all applications in tenant 52270bb2-ed98-4b79-9314-1af808682b4b
### Mirrors what scripts/stage-18-secret-monitor/Get-TenantSecretInventory.ps1
### enumerates in the Stage-18 pipeline.
GET https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/applications
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### Same call, projected to the fields the secret-monitor cares about
GET https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/applications?$select=id,appId,displayName,passwordCredentials,keyCredentials
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
